videos.title: ⬇️ The money mistake we all make in relationships! 💔 #moneytips  #financetips  #savemoney
videos.description:
When you're in a relationship, you want to be a team, right? That's why many couples start commingling their money. But here's the thing - it can take away a sense of freedom, and you may end up resenting each other. And that's the last thing you want in a relationship.

So, here's what you should do instead - determine a percentage of your income that each of you will put into your joint account. That way, if you make different incomes, it's fair to both of you.

This helps you maintain your individuality while having a joint account to make big decisions together. This can be a game-changer in your relationship and it'll help you avoid money-related stress in your relationship. 💑

This is my OPINION. I’d love to hear yours on this topic. Share your thoughts or experiences in the comments! 💬
